Sentencas: The perovskite oxide of La0.6Sr0.4Ti0.3Fe0.7O3-delta (LSTF) is the material used as a cathode for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Molecular weight dependence of ethyl cellulose adsorption behavior on (La, Sr)(Ti, Fe)O3-δ particles in organic solvent pastes and their printing properties

Sentencas: Since the conductivity of a cathode formed via screen printing techniques depends on the conducting particle content in the film after sintering, the paste design is important to obtain the thick film with a high conductivity.
Titulo: Molecular weight dependence of ethyl cellulose adsorption behavior on (La, Sr)(Ti, Fe)O3-δ particles in organic solvent pastes and their printing properties

Sentencas: The effects of the molecular weight of ethyl cellulose (EC) on the paste properties of the LSTF and the densities of printed thick films were investigated.
Titulo: Molecular weight dependence of ethyl cellulose adsorption behavior on (La, Sr)(Ti, Fe)O3-δ particles in organic solvent pastes and their printing properties

Sentencas: EC as a binder was mixed with an organic solvent (diethylene glycol monobutyl ether acetate, BDGAC) and LSTF powder to prepare the paste.
Titulo: Molecular weight dependence of ethyl cellulose adsorption behavior on (La, Sr)(Ti, Fe)O3-δ particles in organic solvent pastes and their printing properties

Sentencas: To understand the conformation of EC in the paste, the intrinsic viscosity ([eta]), hydrodynamic radius (R-H), and Mark-Houwink-Sakurada parameter (alpha) of EC in BDGAC were estimated.
Titulo: Molecular weight dependence of ethyl cellulose adsorption behavior on (La, Sr)(Ti, Fe)O3-δ particles in organic solvent pastes and their printing properties

Sentencas: We also evaluated the conformation of EC on the LSTF particles by using the beta parameter of Perkel and Ullman's equation for the adsorption of EC onto LSTF.
Titulo: Molecular weight dependence of ethyl cellulose adsorption behavior on (La, Sr)(Ti, Fe)O3-δ particles in organic solvent pastes and their printing properties

Sentencas: We revealed that the conformation of EC was a train-loop-tail shape, close to a flat structure and affected the rheological properties and the film densities.
Titulo: Molecular weight dependence of ethyl cellulose adsorption behavior on (La, Sr)(Ti, Fe)O3-δ particles in organic solvent pastes and their printing properties

Sentencas: The highest density of a sintered film was obtained with the paste using 3.0 wt% EC with a molecular weight of 141,000.
Titulo: Molecular weight dependence of ethyl cellulose adsorption behavior on (La, Sr)(Ti, Fe)O3-δ particles in organic solvent pastes and their printing properties
